The paper deals with resource allocation in 5G systems using non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) with successive interference cancellation (SIC). This involves optimizing power and channel allocation for multiple users accessing the same frequency-time resource. The paper provides theoretical insights and algorithmic solutions for this problem, which are likely to fall under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and game theory (cs.GT).
